<HEAD>Woman Cleans Out Attic, Dumps Grenade</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LA SPEZIA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An elderly woman tossed a hand grenade into a garbage dump and announced, `` Enough already, I ca n't keep this in the attic any more,'' authorities said. Police blocked off the area after learning of the incident and eventually fished out the American-made grenade, whose pin had not been removed. No one was injured in the incident Friday in <LOCATION> La </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Spezia </LOCATION>, 200 miles north of <LOCATION> Rome </LOCATION>. After the woman disposed of the grenade, she told bystanders, `` I have thrown it away and now it's up to you,'' the Italian news agency <ORGANIZATION> ANSA </ORGANIZATION> said. The woman left the area and was not found, police said.
