<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Mayor <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Koch </PERSON> told the <ORGANIZATION> Pittsburgh </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pirates </ORGANIZATION> they'll walk the plank in their next series with the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mets </ORGANIZATION>, in another inning _ er, round _ of good-natured goading between <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. When the <ORGANIZATION> Pirates </ORGANIZATION> ran a series of ads two weeks ago calling the <ORGANIZATION> Mets </ORGANIZATION> another good reason to hate <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Koch </PERSON> said of <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION>, `` Where is it?'' <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION> Mayor <PERSON> Sophie </PERSON> <PERSON> Masloff </PERSON> sent <PERSON> Koch </PERSON> a map and reminded him of <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION>'s considerable charms. And <PERSON> Koch </PERSON>, through a television reporter, invited her to lunch in the Big Apple. <PERSON> Koch </PERSON> sent a letter Wednesday to <PERSON> Masloff </PERSON> saying he was `` delighted to learn that <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION> has been designated one of <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'s ` most-livable cities.''' But the designation obviously was made, <PERSON> Koch </PERSON> said, by someone `` with a sense of humor.'' `` I ca n't promise your Buccaneers -LRB- the <ORGANIZATION> Pirates </ORGANIZATION> -RRB- will be walking on a red carpet when they arrive in the Big Apple for their next series with the <ORGANIZATION> Mets </ORGANIZATION>, but we will be looking for an appropriate plank,'' <PERSON> Koch </PERSON> said. The Pirates will be at <LOCATION> Shea </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Stadium </LOCATION> for a four-game series starting July 29. The Mets visit Three Rivers Stadium Aug. 5 for a four-game meeting. <PERSON> Koch </PERSON>'s office released his letter Friday, as well as a letter sent June 30 by <PERSON> Masloff </PERSON> to <PERSON> Koch </PERSON>. <PERSON> Masloff </PERSON> wrote, `` While I felt your comment on <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION>'s location was tongue in cheek _ <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION> having been designated <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'s most-livable city and being the third-largest corporate headquarters in the nation _ just to be on the safe side, I am sending you a map of <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION> `` It would be nice if you could make use of it when the <ORGANIZATION> Mets </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Pirates </ORGANIZATION> tangle here again,'' she added.
