<BYLINE>By DAVID THURBER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Thailand </LOCATION>'s foreign minister said today that an international peacekeeping force could prevent the <ORGANIZATION> Khmer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rouge </ORGANIZATION> from retaking power in <LOCATION> Cambodia </LOCATION> after Vietnamese occupation forces leave. Foreign Minister <PERSON> Siddhi </PERSON> <PERSON> Savetsila </PERSON> said <LOCATION> Thailand </LOCATION> and its <LOCATION> Southeast </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Asian </LOCATION> allies do not want to see a return of the <ORGANIZATION> Khmer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rouge </ORGANIZATION>, who killed up to 3 million people when they ruled <LOCATION> Cambodia </LOCATION> from 1975 until the Vietnamese invasion of 1978. Previously, officials of the <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Southeast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Asian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION>, which strongly backs a three-party resistance coalition that includes the <ORGANIZATION> Khmer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rouge </ORGANIZATION>, did not issue a strong public stand on the issue. <PERSON> Siddhi </PERSON> spoke at a news conference ending a three-day annual conference of foreign ministers of <ORGANIZATION> ASEAN </ORGANIZATION>. `` I think the <ORGANIZATION> Khmer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rouge </ORGANIZATION> know that they can not come back because we do n't support them to come back,'' he said. `` So I think we can use a lot of pressure besides the peacekeeping force. `` They know that <ORGANIZATION> ASEAN </ORGANIZATION> ... is trying to support a resolution of the Cambodian problem by not supporting the return of the <ORGANIZATION> Khmer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rouge </ORGANIZATION>,'' he said. At the same news conference, Secretary of State <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> said that during his upcoming visit to <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>, he plans to stress <LOCATION> America </LOC