ON> Court </ORGANIZATION>, as the suspensions are totally inconsistent with the independence of the judiciary and will lead to the destruction of the judiciary as an independent branch of government,'' the council said. Deputy Prime Minister <PERSON> Abdul </PERSON> <PERSON> Ghafar </PERSON> <PERSON> Baba </PERSON> denied on Friday that politicians were undermining the independence of the judiciary. In February, the high court ruled that <PERSON> Mahathir </PERSON>'s party, the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Malays </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION>, was illegal because it had branches that were not registered with the authorities as required by law. Since then, <PERSON> Mahathir </PERSON> has set up a new party called `` New UMNO'' and has been busy recruiting old members.
