ON> India </LOCATION>, according to the Guinness Book of Records. More than 800 people were killed when a train plunged into a flood-swollen river in the eastern state of <LOCATION> Bihar </LOCATION> in June 1981, <ORGANIZATION> Guinness </ORGANIZATION> said.
