<NOTE>EDS: Leads with 9 grafs to CORRECT that one wounded by gunfire and
another injured by explosive in Jebalya, sted two shot and wounded.
Pickup 7th graf pvs ``The army...''</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By ALLYN FISHER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Israeli soldiers and <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> protesters clashed in street battles across the occupied territories Saturday. One Palestinian was fatally shot, raising the death toll to 217 as the uprising against <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> rule entered its eighth month. A general strike shut down commerce in major cities and towns. Palestinian reports said at least 34 protesters were injured. The army put the figure at 11. Palestinian reporters said soldiers fatally shot 25-year-old <PERSON> Fayek </PERSON> <PERSON> Suleiman </PERSON> <PERSON> Hussein </PERSON> in the heart after opening fire on stone-throwing protesters in <LOCATION> Jebalya </LOCATION> refugee camp in the occupied <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION>. Hospital officials said two people were injured. The army confirmed the death in Jebalya but said it was investigating the circumstances. Officials at <LOCATION> Shifa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> said a woman, <PERSON> Suad </PERSON> <PERSON> Dib </PERSON> <PERSON> Ippbail </PERSON>, 34, was wounded in the hand by gunfire during the clash in <LOCATION> Jebalaya </LOCATION>. A five-year-old boy, <PERSON> Samir </PERSON> <PERSON> Mahmud </PERSON> <PERSON> Zidan </PERSON>, also suffered wounds in the face, left hand and left leg when he played with an explosive during or after the clash, the officials said. It was not immediately known what kind of explosive was involved. Palestinian reporters said earlier that both people injured in Jebalya were wounded by gunfire. In <LOCATION> Arura </LOCATION>, near the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> city of <LOCATION> Ramallah </LOCATION>, witnesses said soldiers beat five demonstrators during a raid and fractured a man's skull by knocking his head against a wall and beating it with a rifle butt. The army said troops detained several stone-throwing youths in <LOCATION> Arura </LOCATION> after chasing them into