up 4th graf pvs, The Piper...</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By MAGGIE JACKSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ABERDEEN, Scotland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Troubleshooter `` Red'' <PERSON> Adair </PERSON> took the first steps Saturday toward capping the wells of a burned-out oil platform. The rig's owner said it might take three weeks to find the bodies of 149 men killed in the <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Sea </LOCATION> disaster. <PERSON> Adair </PERSON>'s men explored the twisted remains of the <ORGANIZATION> Piper </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alpha </ORGANIZATION> platform for about an hour Saturday and used a camera-equipped submersible vessel to assess the damage, said a statement from the platform's owner, Los Angeles-based <ORGANIZATION> Occidental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Occidental </ORGANIZATION> hired <PERSON> Adair </PERSON> to make the rig safe, seal gas leaks and save the oil wells to which the rig is connected The 73-year-old <PERSON> Adair </PERSON>, based in <LOCATION> Houston </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, has gained fame over several decades by capping out-of-control oil wells. `` It seems to me there are three or four wells that are burning ... and two are burning pretty good,'' <PERSON> Adair </PERSON> said after examining the remains of the platform. He said everything was going well `` and we expect to stay on schedule,'' but did not elaborate. `` I'd like to say one thing. ... I've never seen so many safety-conscious people in my life and I think they are doing an excellent job,'' <PERSON> Adair </PERSON> said. The <ORGANIZATION> Piper </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alpha </ORGANIZATION> exploded Wednesday night in a fireball that <ORGANIZATION> Occidental </ORGANIZATION> says may have been caused by a gas leak directly below the living quarters. Sixty-four men escaped. Eighteen remained in the <ORGANIZATION> Aberdeen </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Royal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Infirmary </ORGANIZATION> on Saturday, one in serious condition. Seventeen bodies were recovered befor